This package helps using the command line version of rar and unrar
on linux



Version 0.4: 

Now using rar instead of 7zip, rar has good documentation, but is not open source.


Install this module like this:

    sudo pip install LibRarPython-0.0.x.tar.gz 

(replace x with your version)


You also need rar

On ubuntu:

    sudo aptitude install rar ubrar


Usage example

#!/usr/bin/python
import archive

a = archive.Archive("/home/me/testarchive1.rar")
a.add_file("/home/me/testfile")
a.run() 
  
